in Ostmitteleuropa. Indem sie außerdem die Verflechtung Oppositioneller mit dem Westen einbezieht, erweitert die Arbeit situativ die ostmitteleuropäische Perspektive.  aIn the waning years of socialism, the nation remained the dominant idea of social order in Eastern Europe. In the underground literature of samizdat, oppositional political thinkers in Poland, Czechoslovakia, and Hungary employed this term as they sought models for political community. Thus, they extended their key notions of freedom and human rights beyond ideological contradictions to develop a specific, oppositional concept of the nation.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aOpposition (Political science)zEurope, CentralxHistoryy20th century. 0aOpposition (Political science)zEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 0aUnderground literaturezEurope, Central. 0aUnderground literaturezEurope, Eastern. 4aBegriffsgeschichte. 4aIdeengeschichte. 4aLate socialism. 4aOrdnungsvorstellungen. 4aSpätsozialismus. 4aTransnationale Geschichte. 4aconceptual history. 4aideas of order. 4aintellectual history. 4atransnational history. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2015z9783110438635oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104188660 cprintz978311041977140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041877440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110418774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110418774.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPD